The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                               Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, April 1: The banking cash transaction tax, which imposed a levy on cash drawn from bank, was withdrawn by the government today. Officials said the tax was scrapped as it had served the purpose of enlarging the information system of the income tax department in tracking unaccounted money.                            
	 New Delhi, April 1: A fire broke out today at RILs commissioned oil refinery at Jamnagar in Gujarat, but there were no casualties as the fire was put out swiftly. There was a minor fire in a section of RPL. This has been contained, localised and brought under control... there has been no casualty, a company statement said.                            
	 New Delhi, April 1: The government has deferred the implementation of mandatory provisioning by firms for forex losses and gains on the basis of market value of their financial assets till 2011.                             
	 New Delhi, April 1: Royalty income of foreign firms in India is taxable in full if the firm does not have a permanent establishment here, the Authority for Advance Ruling said.                            
	 Mumbai, April 1: Health insurers can no longer deny renewal of policies on the ground that the insured have made their claim, the Insurance Regulatory and Development Authority said.                                                                                                                           
